{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-02",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_02_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Death in the Fog",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 247.54,
  "page_end_sec": 490.05,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.738,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 247.54,
      "end": 249.9,
      "text": "The building at the other end had a blank grey sidewall",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 250.4,
      "end": 252.54,
      "text": "that looked down on the lot behind the billboard."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.36,
      "end": 255.18,
      "text": "Lights flickered on the sidewall and"
    },
    {
      "start": 255.52,
      "end": 257.44,
      "text": "the shadows of men moving among lights."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.624,
      "end": 260.98,
      "text": "Spade turned from the parapet and walked up",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 260.98,
      "end": 263.64,
      "text": "Bush Street to the alley where men were grouped."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.46,
      "end": 266.86,
      "text": "A uniformed policeman chewing gum under an enameled",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 266.86,
      "end": 270.14,
      "text": "sign that said _Burritt St._ in white against dark blue"
    },
    {
      "start": 270.32,
      "end": 271.72,
      "text": "put out an arm and asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.68,
      "end": 273.5,
      "text": "\"What do you want here?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 274.688,
      "end": 275.52,
      "text": "\"I'm Sam Spade.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 275.64,
      "end": 277.32,
      "text": "Tom Polhaus phoned me.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 277.77,
      "end": 282.18,
      "text": "\"Sure you are.\" The policeman's arm went down. \"I"
    },
    {
      "start": 282.208,
      "end": 284.98,
      "text": "didn't know you at first. Well, they're back there.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 285.24,
      "end": 289.06,
      "text": "He jerked a thumb over his shoulder. \"Bad business.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 290.2,
      "end": 292.8,
      "text": "\"Bad enough,\" Spade agreed, and went up the alley.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 294.112,
      "end": 296.76,
      "text": "Half-way up it, not far from the entrance, a dark",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 296.76,
      "end": 300.0,
      "text": "ambulance stood. Behind the ambulance, to the left,"
    },
    {
      "start": 300.08,
      "end": 302.28,
      "text": "the alley was bounded by a waist-high fence,"
    },
    {
      "start": 302.32,
      "end": 305.96,
      "text": "horizontal strips of rough boarding. From the"
    },
    {
      "start": 306.08,
      "end": 308.38,
      "text": "fence dark ground fell away steeply to"
    },
    {
      "start": 308.384,
      "end": 310.0,
      "text": "the billboard on Stockton Street below."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.18,
      "end": 311.64,
      "text": "A ten-foot",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 311.72,
      "end": 314.2,
      "text": "length of the fence's top rail had been torn from"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.2,
      "end": 317.16,
      "text": "a post at one end and hung dangling from the other."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.304,
      "end": 319.5,
      "text": "Fifteen feet down the slope,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 319.84,
      "end": 321.08,
      "text": "a flat boulder stuck out."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.06,
      "end": 323.74,
      "text": "In the notch between boulder and slope"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.44,
      "end": 325.88,
      "text": "Miles Archer lay on his back."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.82,
      "end": 327.92,
      "text": "Two men stood over him."
    },
    {
      "start": 328.9,
      "end": 330.42,
      "text": "One of them held the beam of an electric"
    },
    {
      "start": 330.58,
      "end": 331.68,
      "text": "torch on the dead man."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.7,
      "end": 334.78,
      "text": "Other men with lights moved up and down the slope."
    },
    {
      "start": 336.08,
      "end": 337.16,
      "text": "One of them hailed Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 337.56,
      "end": 337.98,
      "text": "\"Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 338.12,
      "end": 338.36,
      "text": "Sam,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 338.58,
      "end": 340.82,
      "text": "and clambered up to the alley,"
    },
    {
      "start": 341.24,
      "end": 343.42,
      "text": "his shadow running up the slope before him."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.42,
      "end": 347.28,
      "text": "He was a barrel-bellied tall man with shrewd small eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 347.82,
      "end": 348.4,
      "text": "a thick mouth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.58,
      "end": 350.72,
      "text": "and carelessly shaven dark jowls."
    },
    {
      "start": 351.52,
      "end": 351.92,
      "text": "His shoes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 351.94,
      "end": 352.22,
      "text": "knees,"
    },
    {
      "start": 352.34,
      "end": 352.72,
      "text": "hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 352.74,
      "end": 354.96,
      "text": "and chin were daubed with brown loam."
    },
    {
      "start": 356.02,
      "end": 358.36,
      "text": "\"I figured you'd want to see it before we took him away,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 358.92,
      "end": 361.0,
      "text": "he said as he stepped over the broken fence."
    },
    {
      "start": 361.94,
      "end": 362.48,
      "text": "\"Thanks,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 362.56,
      "end": 362.76,
      "text": "Tom,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 362.96,
      "end": 363.66,
      "text": "Spade said."
    },
    {
      "start": 364.3,
      "end": 364.7,
      "text": "\"What happened?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 366.08,
      "end": 368.66,
      "text": "He put an elbow on a fence-post and looked down at the men below,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 369.28,
      "end": 370.66,
      "text": "nodding to those who nodded to him."
    },
    {
      "start": 371.4,
      "end": 373.98,
      "text": "Tom Polhaus poked his own left breast with a dirty finger.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 374.88,
      "end": 376.72,
      "text": "\"Got him right through the pump—with this.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 377.72,
      "end": 381.02,
      "text": "He took a fat revolver from his coat-pocket and held it out to Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 382.016,
      "end": 384.28,
      "text": "Mud inlaid the depressions in the revolver's surface."
    },
    {
      "start": 385.18,
      "end": 385.74,
      "text": "\"A Webley.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 386.06,
      "end": 386.5,
      "text": "English,"
    },
    {
      "start": 386.68,
      "end": 387.06,
      "text": "ain't it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 387.84,
      "end": 389.5,
      "text": "Spade took his elbow from the fence-post",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 389.5,
      "end": 391.14,
      "text": "and leaned down to look at the weapon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.8,
      "end": 392.78,
      "text": "but he did not touch it."
    },
    {
      "start": 393.44,
      "end": 393.98,
      "text": "\"Yes,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 394.12,
      "end": 394.62,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 395.232,
      "end": 397.06,
      "text": "\"Webley-Fosbery automatic revolver."
    },
    {
      "start": 397.16,
      "end": 398.24,
      "text": "That's it."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.38,
      "end": 398.82,
      "text": "Thirty-eight,"
    },
    {
      "start": 399.08,
      "end": 399.48,
      "text": "eight shot."
    },
    {
      "start": 400.32,
      "end": 401.32,
      "text": "They don't make them any more."
    },
    {
      "start": 401.98,
      "end": 403.28,
      "text": "How many gone out of it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 404.34,
      "end": 404.72,
      "text": "\"One pill.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 404.98,
      "end": 406.56,
      "text": "Tom poked his breast again."
    },
    {
      "start": 407.18,
      "end": 408.6,
      "text": "\"He must've been dead when"
    },
    {
      "start": 408.6,
      "end": 409.34,
      "text": "he cracked the fence.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 410.08,
      "end": 411.78,
      "text": "He raised the muddy revolver."
    },
    {
      "start": 412.56,
      "end": 413.38,
      "text": "\"Ever seen this before?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 414.656,
      "end": 415.34,
      "text": "Spade nodded.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 415.78,
      "end": 417.34,
      "text": "\"I've seen Webley-Fosberys,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 417.82,
      "end": 418.76,
      "text": "he said without interest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 418.96,
      "end": 420.36,
      "text": "and then spoke rapidly:"
    },
    {
      "start": 421.2,
      "end": 421.76,
      "text": "\"He was shot",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 421.92,
      "end": 422.16,
      "text": "up here,"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.26,
      "end": 422.44,
      "text": "huh?"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.71,
      "end": 424.24,
      "text": "Standing where you are,"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.52,
      "end": 425.48,
      "text": "with his back to the fence."
    },
    {
      "start": 426.34,
      "end": 427.22,
      "text": "The man that shot him stands"
    },
    {
      "start": 427.22,
      "end": 427.56,
      "text": "here.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 428.5,
      "end": 430.62,
      "text": "He went around in front of Tom and raised a hand,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 430.64,
      "end": 431.2,
      "text": "breast-high,"
    },
    {
      "start": 431.38,
      "end": 432.62,
      "text": "with leveled forefinger."
    },
    {
      "start": 433.34,
      "end": 434.04,
      "text": "\"Lets him have it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 434.34,
      "end": 435.22,
      "text": "and Miles goes back,"
    },
    {
      "start": 435.51,
      "end": 438.6,
      "text": "taking the top off the fence and going on through,"
    },
    {
      "start": 439.02,
      "end": 440.72,
      "text": "and down till the rock catches him."
    },
    {
      "start": 441.3,
      "end": 441.6,
      "text": "That it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 442.752,
      "end": 443.02,
      "text": "\"That's it,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 443.22,
      "end": 444.4,
      "text": "Tom replied slowly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 445.216,
      "end": 446.22,
      "text": "working his brows together."
    },
    {
      "start": 446.62,
      "end": 448.36,
      "text": "\"The blast burnt his coat.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 448.97,
      "end": 450.16,
      "text": "\"Who found him?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 450.82,
      "end": 452.76,
      "text": "\"The man on the beat, Shilling. He"
    },
    {
      "start": 453.792,
      "end": 456.94,
      "text": "was coming down Bush, and just as he got here a machine turning"
    },
    {
      "start": 457.14,
      "end": 459.88,
      "text": "threw headlights up here and he saw the top off"
    },
    {
      "start": 459.88,
      "end": 462.64,
      "text": "the fence so he came up to look at it and found"
    },
    {
      "start": 462.72,
      "end": 465.58,
      "text": "him. What about the machine that was turning around?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 466.8,
      "end": 469.52,
      "text": "\"Not a damned thing about it, Sam. Shilling didn't pay",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 469.52,
      "end": 472.2,
      "text": "any attention to it, not knowing anything was wrong"
    },
    {
      "start": 472.2,
      "end": 475.52,
      "text": "then. He says nobody didn't come out of here while"
    },
    {
      "start": 475.8,
      "end": 478.2,
      "text": "he was coming down from Powell or he'd've seen them."
    },
    {
      "start": 478.71,
      "end": 480.78,
      "text": "The only other way out would be under the"
    },
    {
      "start": 480.92,
      "end": 481.76,
      "text": "billboard on Stockton."
    },
    {
      "start": 481.94,
      "end": 483.44,
      "text": "Nobody went that way."
    },
    {
      "start": 483.72,
      "end": 486.84,
      "text": "The fog's got the ground soggy, and the only marks"
    },
    {
      "start": 487.14,
      "end": 490.05,
      "text": "are where Miles slid down and where this here gun rolled.\""
    }
  ]
}
